replyContent:
On most Android devices, the media volume (such as the volume of an audio pronunciation) can only be raised when that content is being used (i.e. when the pronunciation is playing). 

To raise the volume for audio pronunciations, try playing the pronunciation of a long word and then increasing the volume simultaneously as the word is playing.
